<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391150>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–4. Asindulum heads, males. 1. A. coxale, anterior. 2. A. coxale, lateral. 3. A. montanum, anterior. 4. A. montanum, lateral. Scale bars = ca. 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: asp, anterior spiracle; clyp, clypeus; cx1, coxa 1; hyphar, hypopharynx; lab, labium, lbl, labellum; lbr, labrum; mx, maxilla; plp, palpus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391150/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391179>
    dc:description "FIGURE 38. Asindulum montanum, male habitus. Scale = ca. 1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391179/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391189>
    dc:description "FIGURES 47–50.Asindulum montanum, female terminalia and abdomen. 47.Terminalia, dorsal. 48. Terminalia, posteroventral. 49. Terminalia, posterolateral. 50. Abdomen, dorsal. Scale for Figs. 47–49 = ca. 0.25 mm and for Fig. 50 = ca. 1.0 mm Abbreviations: ce, cercus; s8, sternite 8; s10, sternite 10; t7, tergite 7." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391189/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

